Easily distinguished from known congeners by shapes of procursus ( Figs 886–889 ; distal ventral spine proximally undulating, large prolateral membranous structure), genital bulb ( Figs 892–897 ; distinctive shape of apophysis, with large whitish area on retrolateral-ventral side), and by female internal genitalia ( Fig. 891 ; distinctive transversal sclerite in front of whitish triangular area; pore plates long and narrow, in vertical position). From most species also by ventral process on male palpal femur ( Fig. 879 ; present but smaller in
P. salmeronica González-Sponga, 1999
).
